---
const points = [
  {
    n: "01",
    title: "SwiftUI semantics, not a clone",
    body:
      "Recursive parent-child layout. Graph-scoped state drives rendering, not the reverse. Modifier order matters because modifiers participate in layout and semantics. The terminal target does not bend the authoring story.",
    sym: "@MainActor · View · @State · Layout",
  },
  {
    n: "02",
    title: "One app. Several host products.",
    body:
      "The same App and Scene declarations can feed a terminal executable, a WASI browser deployment, a localhost WebHost launch, or a host-managed SwiftUI surface. The framework owns the cells; the host owns the chrome.",
    sym: "SwiftTUI · SwiftTUIWASI · SwiftTUIWebHostCLI · SwiftUIHost",
  },
  {
    n: "03",
    title: "Strict, inspectable pipeline",
    body:
      "Seven phases — resolve, measure, place, semantics, draw, raster, commit — enforced by DefaultRenderer, FrameArtifacts, and the regression suites. Inspect any phase in tests; snapshot any frame; diff any commit.",
    sym: "DefaultRenderer · FrameArtifacts",
  },
  {
    n: "04",
    title: "Capability-aware, not lowest-common-denominator",
    body:
      "ANSI, sanitized OSC 8 hyperlinks, Kitty graphics, Sixel, truecolor, and mouse reporting are negotiated per session against a live capability profile. PNG and baseline JPEG decode in pure Swift; GIF playback ships in the AnimatedImage peer product.",
    sym: "TerminalCapabilityProfile",
  },
  {
    n: "05",
    title: "Swift 6 package internals",
    body:
      "The package builds in Swift 6 language mode with strict memory-safety settings, explicit @MainActor authoring APIs, and real Sendable boundaries. App packages choose their own policy.",
    sym: "Swift 6 · @MainActor View.body · Sendable artifacts",
  },
  {
    n: "06",
    title: "No dependencies on a terminal emulator",
    body:
      "The browser path does not embed xterm.js or a DOM terminal. WebHost mounts a scene runtime directly. Tests render frames as integer-cell rasters without spinning up a TTY.",
    sym: "WebHost · RasterSurface · no xterm.js",
  },
];
---
<section class="why" id="why">
  <div class="shell">
    <header class="head">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="num">/00</span>Why this exists</span>
      <h2>Built for engineers who want SwiftUI's authoring model in places SwiftUI doesn't ship.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Most TUI frameworks invent a new authoring model for the terminal.
        SwiftTUI keeps the SwiftUI authoring model and reinterprets the
        substrate. Same <span class="mono">View</span>, <span class="mono">@State</span>,
        <span class="mono">@FocusState</span>, <span class="mono">PreferenceKey</span>,
        and <span class="mono">Layout</span> protocol you already know — drawn
        as integer-cell glyphs instead of CoreAnimation layers.
      </p>
    </header>

    <ol class="grid mono" aria-label="differentiators">
      {points.map((p) => (
        <li class="card">
          <div class="card-head">
            <span class="ix">{p.n}</span>
            <h3>{p.title}</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="body">{p.body}</p>
          <div class="sym">{p.sym}</div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .why {
    padding: 96px 0 56px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    margin-top: 64px;
  }
  .head { max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 56px; }
  .head h2 { margin-top: 16px; }
  .head .lede { margin-top: 18px; max-width: 70ch; }

  .grid {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  }
  .card {
    position: relative;
    padding: 26px 22px 22px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    min-height: 220px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0.012) 100%);
  }
  .card:nth-child(3n) { border-right: 0; }
  .card:nth-last-child(-n+3) { border-bottom: 0; }
  .card-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .ix {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    color: var(--ink-4);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
  }
  .card h3 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 540;
    letter-spacing: -0.012em;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .card .body {
    margin-top: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 13.5px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .card .sym {
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: 18px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--line);
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1080px) {
    .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
    .card:nth-child(3n) { border-right: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .card:nth-child(2n) { border-right: 0; }
    .card:nth-last-child(-n+3) { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .card:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: 0; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .card { border-right: 0 !important; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line) !important; }
    .card:last-child { border-bottom: 0 !important; }
  }
</style>
